                            <comment id="88512" author="rwinch" created="Wed, 6 Mar 2013 08:54:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like you are encountering a bad error message (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2143&quot; title=&quot;Error message still mentioning version 3.1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-2143&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-2143&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). To get past the error change your schema declaration to be spring-security-3.2.xsd. If you do not want to do this every update, you should simply update to spring-security.xsd which uses the current version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88718" author="rwinch" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 07:08:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is technically a duplicate since the underlying problem is the invalid error message&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88719" author="rwinch" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 07:08:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing as duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2143&quot; title=&quot;Error message still mentioning version 3.1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-2143&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-2143&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; due to no further feedback&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88838" author="mooshben" created="Mon, 18 Mar 2013 02:41:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Rob,&lt;br/&gt;
Sorry, I was away for a while and couldn&apos;t reply.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Changing to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/schema/security/spring-security.xsd&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.springframework.org/schema/security/spring-security.xsd&lt;/a&gt; fixed the problem, thanks!&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/schema/security/spring-security-3.2.xsd&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.springframework.org/schema/security/spring-security-3.2.xsd&lt;/a&gt; is not online, so I can&apos;t use it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When do you expect M2/RC1 to be released? it&apos;s kind of scary using the snapshot version.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Thanks for all your help!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88846" author="rwinch" created="Mon, 18 Mar 2013 06:21:04 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Changing to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/schema/security/spring-security.xsd&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.springframework.org/schema/security/spring-security.xsd&lt;/a&gt; fixed the problem, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Glad that helped&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/schema/security/spring-security-3.2.xsd&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.springframework.org/schema/security/spring-security-3.2.xsd&lt;/a&gt; is not online, so I can&apos;t use it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We don&apos;t push XSD&apos;s to production until the release. The URLs do not need to be resolved since Java will resolve them off the classpath too. Alternatively, you can find the various XSDs at this location &lt;a href=&quot;http://static.springsource.org/autorepo/schema/spring-security/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://static.springsource.org/autorepo/schema/spring-security/&lt;/a&gt; Please note the location is subject to change without regard to passivity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;When do you expect M2/RC1 to be released? it&apos;s kind of scary using the snapshot version.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t have an exact date, but I expect it to be out within the next month. It really depends on how the Spring Security Java Config shapes up. The best bet is to keep an eye on the JIRA road map which will stay up to date.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88850" author="mooshben" created="Mon, 18 Mar 2013 07:13:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks a lot!&lt;br/&gt;
Looking forward to M2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
